Located in three dialect groups in China: (a) Szechuan, western and central Kuei-chou, eastern Yün, western part of the Autonomous Region for the Chuang people in Kuang-hsi (Punu perhaps identified with this group); (b) Hua-yüan, Feng-huang, Chi-shou, Ku-chang, Lu-hsi, Pao-ching districts in Hunan, and the Sung-t'ao Autonomous District for the Miao people in Kuei-chou; (c) K'ai-li, Lei-shan, Ma-chiang, Huang-p'ing, Chin-p'ing, Li-p'ing, Ts'ung-chiang, Jung-chiang districts in Kuei-chou, the Ta-miao-shan Autonomous District for the Miao people and the San-chiang Autonomous District for the Kam people in Kuang-hsi, and in the T'ung-tao Autonomous District for the Kam people in Hunan.
